result.execSummary:
The defendant Yvette L. Brown was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court fines and costs are due as follows:  $100.00 is due on or before 08/01/2022 and then $100.00 is due on the first of each month thereafter until paid in full. A $15.00 payment plan fee has been added. Failure to pay court ordered fine and costs will result in a civil judgment being entered for collection purposes.

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.

10:28 AM Defendant Yvette L. Brown in court.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Lucas Swank in court for Yvette L. Brown. Defendant enters a plea of No Contest. Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  She understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. She understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer contrary to 946.41(1). 

Joint Recommendation: $50.00 fine plus costs (totaling $516.00) Defendant will update address with the court. Defendant did not exercise her right to allocution. 

Court adopts the joint recommendation: Orders $50 fine plus costs totaling $516.00. Pay @ $100.00 a month, starting 8/1, pay each month thereafter until paid in full. Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.
